 Port Elizabeth - Despatch police are seeking help from the public in solving a double murder case after two men were fatally shot in an apparent drive-by shooting in front of a tavern in Despatch on Friday night. "On Friday, at around 11:30pm, it is alleged that at least one passenger in a white VW Polo fired several shots at the two men, who were standing on the roadside as the vehicle drove past," said police spokesperson, Sergeant Majola Nkohli. "The incident occurred in front of a tavern in Xolile Bottoman Street, Despatch. "One of the victims died at the scene, while a second one ran to the premises of a house opposite a tavern, where he collapsed and died." He said that the names of the deceased are Skhumbuzo Lucas (42) and Xolani Skweyiya (43). "Police are urging anyone with information that could lead to the arrest of the suspects to contact the investigating officer, Detective Sergeant Leigh Jacobs at 074 999 8707," Sgt Nkohli said. "The information may also be shared anonymously via Crime Stop 08600 10111." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  